Being level 20 signifies many things.  To some, it is the end of a long
journey.  To others, it is the beginning of a new adventure.  Still others
feel it is the gateway to wizship.  But...if you are having fun playing,
why leave the game?  Thus, we at Darkwind are proud to present the Nobles
System!  At level 20, with 500 quest points and 50,000 gold, you can become
a full fledged noble.  You get a castle, plus the opportunity to increase
your power by various means.  Castles will not directly increase your 
power, though with certain additions, you will be able to have services
that you and you alone possess.  You can recruit others to your castle.
If you have a large castle with lots of services, you may be able to charge
a significant amount of money for each player in your service.  You can
attack other castles and steal their flags.  You can build towns and raise
armies to march against your enemies.  Grow in financial and military
power until you are ready to take on the King!  Many surprises await those
who join the Nobles system, though be warned: A player who joins the 
Nobles and enjoyes the advantages of being part of a Noble's house
can be pk'ed at anytime, for any reason.  You are safe in the castle,
but nowhere else.  Also be warned that this does not give you the right
to pk non-noble players, unless they provoke the attack.
We hope you enjoy the Nobles, and be sure to always keep your eye on
new additions, and modifications.
